  </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Leatherfoot Bags</span><hr size=1> Cuin is level 232 last time I saw, if you are determined to get this bag.   He is the only halfling I know even close to making these, as far as I know.  I would suggest going out and getting as many of the expensive ingredients needed yourself (Mainly, BD's, 4 if you need the 10 slot) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tayfuun>Tayfuun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/20/02 11:53:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=58.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Leatherfoot Bags</span><hr size=1> actually with the new drops of blue diamonds the price is coming down rapidly.  They are about 1.5k at the moment and often sell for less than 1k.  So using 4 bought at 1k each you still have 1250pp before going over the current price of a tink bag.<br>
